name: goodnight moon
description:
There was a man tasked
With opening a wound in my back
Every night

I would brush my teeth
And he would diligently carve the inside of the wound
To ensure the blood would saturate my pajamas
Before waking in the morning
So I could open my eyes to the smell
Of healing flesh

Sometimes whistling over the sound of groaning skin
Or weeping at the inconsequence of his scalpel

Delicately prying the chewed slot
As though peering through an old envelope
I trusted his proficiency in this matter
Because of his own visible sores
Which appeared adequately dismantled

He told me one day I could reach the wound alone and I wouldn’t need him anymore
To prevent the scabbing I resented

But until then
He didn’t mind helping too much
